The Border Guard Unit (BGU) ensures the security of Ghana's international borders and entry and exit points against [[illegal immigration]] and cross-border [[criminal]]s.<ref name="The Formative Stage">{{cite web|url=http://www.ghanaimmigration.org/BPU2.htm|title=The Formative Stage of the Border Patrol Unit (BPU)|work=Ghanaimmigration.org|publisher=|accessdate=27 April 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502080632/http://www.ghanaimmigration.org/BPU2.htm|archivedate=2 May 2014|df=}}</ref> Its tasks include:
* Physical [[patrolling]] of international [[border]]s 
* Preventing [[illegal emigration]]
* Preventing [[drug trafficking]] and [[human trafficking]] 
* Preventing cross-border [[smuggling]]
* Preventing [[wildlife smuggling]] 
* Reporting on suspected subversive activities 
* Preparedness to act as the first line of defence against external aggressors

===Border patrol operations and corporate operations===
[[File:FSM Major CWO âˆ’ Dickson Owusu.jpg|thumb|upright|right|[[Sergeant Major]] and [[Chief Warrant Officer]] Dickson Owusu; the current [[Director-general]] of the BGU (Border Guard Unit)]]
The BGU's primary operation is detection and apprehension of [[illegal aliens]] and smugglers of aliens at or near the land [[border]]s.<ref name="The Formative Stage"/> Some of the major BGU operational activities include maintaining traffic checkpoints and [[security checkpoint]]s along [[highways]] ([[Ghana Road Network]]) leading from [[border]] areas, conducting snap checks and anti-[[smuggling]] within Ghana.<ref name="The Formative Stage"/> These BGU operational activities are performed with the use of [[UCAV]]s, [[UAV]]s, [[attack helicopter]]s, [[armoured fighting vehicle]]s, pick-up [[vehicle]]s, and all purpose [[motorbike]]s .<ref name="The Formative Stage"/> 

===Customs operations===
The BGU physically examines containerized goods at [[Boankra Inland Port]], [[Akosombo Port]], [[Takoradi Harbour]] and [[Tema Harbour]].<ref name="CEPS"/> BGU is working to streamline and fully automate customs processes and procedures under the Ghana Customs Management System (GCMS) and the Ghana Community Network (GCNET).<ref name="CEPS"/>

